        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on the topic of </span><span class=\"english\">“Journey of an Astronaut”.</span><span class=\"english\">                            10</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Journey of an Astronaut</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The journey of an astronaut is adventurous, inspiring, and full of challenges. To achieve this dream, an astronaut must study science, mathematics, and engineering for many years. They also receive special physical training and learn survival skills to face unknown dangers in space. Before the mission, astronauts go through medical tests and use simulators to get used to weightlessness. The rocket launch is the most thrilling part, when they leave Earth and </span><span class=\"english\">enter  space</span><span class=\"english\">. While in orbit, they conduct experiments, repair satellites, and collect important scientific data about the universe. Life in space is very different, as food, sleep, and movement are not the same as on Earth. They must exercise daily to stay healthy and remain calm in the tiny spacecraft. After completing their mission, astronauts return to Earth as true heroes. Their journey inspires all of humanity to dream bigger and explore the mysteries of the universe.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Highest Marks ----------------------------------------------------------------09 Marks</span><span> </span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Journey of an Astronaut</span><span class=\"english\">) ---------</span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> -------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The journey of an astronaut is adventurous, inspiring, and full of challenges. </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) </span><span class=\"english\">Astronaut Training and Mission (Any 06) </span><span class=\"english\">---------------------------------06 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Astronauts study science, mathematics, and engineering for years.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Special physical training and survival skills are provided.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Medical tests and simulators are conducted before mission.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Rocket launch is the thrilling part of the mission.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• In orbit, astronauts conduct experiments, repair satellites, and collect scientific data.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Life in space differs from Earth, requiring daily exercise.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• After mission completion, astronauts return to Earth as heroes.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion </span><span class=\"english\">-----------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">The journey of an astronaut inspires all of humanity to dream bigger and explore the mysteries of the universe.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para)</span><span class=\"english\">.</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span><span> </span><span> </span></p>"
    },
