        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Horizon = As the sun began to rise, a golden light spread across the </span><span class=\"english\">horizon</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Aerosol = She sprayed an aerosol in the room to get rid of mosquitoes.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Disintegrate = The plane disintegrated</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">after crashing into the sea.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Damage = Any damage to the retina could cause permanent blindness.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Pile = The huge pile of clothes on the bed needed folding.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions: </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">i</span><span class=\"english\">) Any correct and logically meaningful sentence will be accepted. (</span><span class=\"english\">Sentences with weak meaning will not be allowed.)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii) For any grammatical or structural mistake, full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Examiners have to show and correct the mistake(s) in the scripts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(iii) For 02 spelling mistakes, 01 mark will be deducted, for 01 spelling mistake, </span><span class=\"english\">0.5 marks will be deducted from that very sentence.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎(iv) For changing the part of speech of the given word by adding a suffix or prefix, the full marks have to be deducted from the very number. But students can use any form if the given word is a verb (depending on the subject-verb agreement, tense, person, number, etc.).</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Use the given word without changing its parts of speech.</span></p>"
